eed Sobowale In April 15, according to a report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), the number of people infected by the coronavirus disease (COVID-19) was 407 while only 12 sadly lost their lives. On the good side, 128 of the total cases as at then recovered… May 16, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" By Rasheed Sobowale Looking back a month ago, the number of confirmed coronavirus cases in Nigeria was lesser than half of a thousand. In April 15, according to a report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), the number of people infected by the coronavirus disease (COVID-19) was 407… May 16, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"